  "prompt": "What online stores accept food stamps for delivery in FL?",
  "response": "Several online retailers accept SNAP EBT for online grocery delivery in Florida. Here are some of the most common options:\n\n*   **Walmart:** Accepts SNAP EBT online and in-store for eligible grocery items.\n*   **Amazon:** Accepts SNAP EBT in Florida for eligible grocery items through Amazon Pantry and Amazon Fresh.\n*   **ALDI (via Instacart):** ALDI partners with Instacart to allow SNAP EBT payments online.\n*   **Publix (via Instacart):** Publix partners with Instacart to allow SNAP EBT payments online.\n*   **FreshDirect:** Accepts SNAP EBT payments online in select areas. Check their website to confirm availability in your specific location.\n*   **BJ's Wholesale Club:** Accepts SNAP EBT online and in-store for eligible grocery items.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Delivery Fees & Minimums:** Be aware of delivery fees and order minimums that may apply.\n*   **Eligible Items:** SNAP EBT can only be used for eligible food items, excluding non-food items like household supplies, alcohol, and pet food.\n*   **Specific Locations:** Availability may vary depending on your exact location in Florida. Check the retailer's website or app to confirm service in your area.\n*   **Third-Party Delivery Services:** When using third-party delivery services like Instacart, check their specific policies regarding SNAP EBT payments, as they may differ from the store's in-store policy.\n\nTo ensure accuracy and the most up-to-date information, I recommend visiting the websites or apps of the specific retailers you are interested in and looking for their SNAP EBT policies or contacting their customer service departments.",
